<!-- tax-02-checklist-organizer.hbs -->
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Tax Season Is Open — Tax Organizer + Checklist</title>
  </head>

  <body
    style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; padding: 20px;"
  >
    <table
      style="max-width:600px; width:100%; margin:auto; border-collapse: collapse;"
    >
      <tr>
        <td style="padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">

          <img
            src="cid:emailHeader"
            width="600"
            style="display:block;width:100%;max-width:600px;height:auto;"
            alt="Tax Season Is Open"
          />

          <h2 style="color: #2a7ae2;">Hi {{name}},</h2>

          <h3 style="margin-top: 10px;">
            Tax season is now open — the IRS is accepting 2025 returns.
          </h3>

          <p>
            If you’re ready to file your
            <strong>2025 federal return</strong>, now is a great time to get
            organized. Filing earlier can help you avoid last‑minute document
            scrambling and reduces the risk of delays from missing forms.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Your 2025 Tax Organizer is attached</strong>
            to make this simple. Below is a short “essentials” checklist of the
            most common items to gather.
          </p>

          <p style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <strong>Quick note:</strong>
            If you think you’ll owe, filing on time still matters. Paying in
            full is ideal when possible — and if you can’t, there may be options
            to discuss. If you’re still waiting on a form, it’s often better to
            file accurately than rush and fix it later.
          </p>

          <table
            role="presentation"
            cellpadding="0"
            cellspacing="0"
            border="0"
            style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin-top: 14px;"
          >
            <tr>
              <th
                align="left"
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5; font-size:14px;"
              >Document</th>
              <th
                align="left"
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5; font-size:14px;"
              >Where to find it + typical timing (2026)</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td
                style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;"
              >W-2</td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                Employer mail/HR portal — usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                1099s (NEC/MISC/INT/DIV)
              </td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                Payers + bank portals — usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                Mortgage interest (Form 1098)
              </td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                Lender portal/mail — usually by
                <strong>Jan 31, 2026</strong>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                Estimated tax payment records
              </td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0;">
                IRS account + bank statements — review by
                <strong>Feb 2026</strong>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px;">Dependent info + filing preferences</td>
              <td style="padding:8px 10px;">
                Prior return + SSNs/DOBs/childcare info — have ready by
                <strong>Jan 2026</strong>.
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>

          <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
            If you want, we can quickly confirm you have what you need — and
            tell you what to prioritize next based on your situation.
          </p>

          <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: bold;">
            Call our consultant help line at
            <a
              href="tel:+1 {{phone}}"
              style="color: #2a7ae2; text-decoration: none;"
            >{{phone}}</a>. When submitting documents, please send them to
            {{processingEmail}}.
          </p>

          <div style="margin-top: 30px;">
            {{{signature}}}
          </div>

          <p style="margin-top: 18px; font-size: 12px; color: #777;">
            General information only — not tax or legal advice.
          </p>

        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>